In December 2007, it became known that the French automotive corporation Renault plans to acquire a 25% stake in AvtoVAZ OJSC [19]. On February 29, 2008, the transaction took place, the share sale agreement was signed by the head of the board of directors of Troika Dialog Investment Company Ruben Vardanyan, Sergey Skvortsov, president of Troika Capital Partners, and Carlos Ghosn, head of the Renault-Nissan corporation[20]. redemption of the treasury shares of the Renault plant will receive a controlling stake. As a result, in September 2008, the main shareholders of the company were: Renault (25%), Russian Technologies (25.1%) and Troika Dialog (25.64%)[ 21].